WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:21.000
Cheetah presents Halloween Horror by Gina D. B. Clement.

00:21.000 --> 00:26.000
Chapter 1 Salem

00:26.000 --> 00:31.000
Salem is a beautiful American town in Massachusetts, USA.

00:31.000 --> 00:36.000
Naum Keog, city of peace, is its Indian name.

00:36.000 --> 00:43.000
But it is also called the Witch City, because of the witch hangings of 1692.

00:43.000 --> 00:48.000
There are seven historical witch museums in Salem.

00:48.000 --> 00:55.000
They all have a lot of information on the witches and hangings of 1692.

00:55.000 --> 01:00.000
Kelly and Meghan Connor are two sisters.

01:00.000 --> 01:03.000
They come from San Francisco, California.

01:03.000 --> 01:11.000
The Connor family now lives in Salem, because Mr. Connor teaches French at the University of Boston.

01:11.000 --> 01:16.000
Kelly is 14, and Meghan is 13.

01:16.000 --> 01:20.000
They go to Salem Middle School, and they like it.

01:20.000 --> 01:23.000
Kelly has red hair and blue eyes.

01:23.000 --> 01:27.000
She's tall and plays basketball for the school team.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
Meghan has fair hair and blue eyes.

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
She's a champion swimmer.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.000
She is a member of the Salem Swimming Team.

01:36.000 --> 01:43.000
It's Friday, October 28, and Halloween is on Monday, October 31.

01:43.000 --> 01:48.000
Kelly and Meghan are very excited, because they love Halloween.

01:48.000 --> 01:53.000
This is their first Halloween in Salem, the Witch City.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
I think about Halloween all the time.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
Says Meghan.

01:56.000 --> 01:57.000
Me too.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
Says Kelly.

01:59.000 --> 02:03.000
We must buy a pumpkin and make a jack-o'-lantern.

02:03.000 --> 02:04.000
Says their mother.

02:04.000 --> 02:11.000
Now finish your breakfast. It's late. School starts in 20 minutes.

02:11.000 --> 02:15.000
The girls eat their eggs and drink their milk.

02:15.000 --> 02:18.000
Then they go upstairs to brush their teeth.

02:18.000 --> 02:21.000
They're ready at quarter past eight.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
Goodbye, Mom. Don't forget to buy the pumpkin.

02:25.000 --> 02:29.000
Okay, goodbye, girls.

02:29.000 --> 02:33.000
Kelly and Meghan always walk to school.

02:33.000 --> 02:40.000
They meet their friends, Susan Garcia, Nick Lee, and Bill Goldberg.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
I'm so excited about Halloween.

02:42.000 --> 02:46.000
Says Susan. Susan is Hispanic American.

02:46.000 --> 02:50.000
She is 13 years old and has long black hair.

02:50.000 --> 02:54.000
This is the first time we can have a party without our parents.

02:54.000 --> 02:59.000
We must find a place to have the party.

02:59.000 --> 03:03.000
Says Nick. He is 14 years old, and he's a good cook.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
His parents have a Chinese restaurant in Salem.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.000
Let's see.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.000
Says Bill, I can ask my grandmother.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
Bill Goldberg is a handsome boy of 14.

03:14.000 --> 03:17.000
His favorite school subject is science.

03:17.000 --> 03:19.000
He lives with his grandmother.

03:19.000 --> 03:23.000
Susan, do you have a scary costume for Halloween?

03:23.000 --> 03:24.000
Asks Kelly.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
It's a surprise. I can't tell you.

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
Says Susan.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
Do you believe in ghosts?

03:30.000 --> 03:31.000
Bill asks.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.000
Yes.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.000
They all say.

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
Oh, I don't.

03:35.000 --> 03:38.000
Bill, science can explain everything.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.000
Really?

03:39.000 --> 03:40.000
Says Nick.

03:40.000 --> 03:43.000
A lot of strange things happen on Halloween night.

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
My grandparents come from China.

03:45.000 --> 03:49.000
They believe in ghosts and evil spirits, too.

03:49.000 --> 03:51.000
Bill laughs.

03:51.000 --> 03:55.000
Do you remember the story of the old woman in the cemetery?

03:55.000 --> 03:58.000
Oh, Nick. Please don't tell us again.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
Says Bill.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
Nick smiles mysteriously.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
It's 8.30 a.m.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
and the school bell is ringing.

04:17.000 --> 04:18.000
Chapter Two.

04:18.000 --> 04:21.000
The Witch Museum.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.000
School finishes at 3.30 p.m.

04:29.000 --> 04:33.000
Kelly and Megan meet their friends outside.

04:33.000 --> 04:36.000
Do you have any ideas for our Halloween party?

04:36.000 --> 04:37.000
Kelly asks.

04:37.000 --> 04:38.000
No, I don't.

04:38.000 --> 04:39.000
Says Susan.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.000
I have an idea.

04:41.000 --> 04:42.000
Says Megan.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
Let's visit one of the Salem Witch Museums.

04:44.000 --> 04:47.000
We can get many ideas from there.

04:47.000 --> 04:49.000
That's a good idea.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.000
Says Susan.

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
There are a lot of scary things there.

04:53.000 --> 04:57.000
Remember, Salem is the Witch City.

04:57.000 --> 05:01.000
At the museum, there are pictures of the witch hangings.

05:01.000 --> 05:05.000
There are also the names of the Salem Witches of 1692.

05:05.000 --> 05:09.000
We can read about their terrible magic.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
Oh, how exciting!

05:11.000 --> 05:12.000
Oh, how exciting!

05:12.000 --> 05:13.000
Say Megan and Kelly.

05:13.000 --> 05:14.000
Let's go.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
Says Susan.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
The girls call Nick and Bill.

05:18.000 --> 05:21.000
Together, the five friends go to the museum.

05:21.000 --> 05:24.000
When they arrive, it's late.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
How many tickets do you want?

05:26.000 --> 05:27.000
Asks the attendant.

05:27.000 --> 05:29.000
Five tickets, please.

05:29.000 --> 05:30.000
Says Bill.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
That's $10.

05:32.000 --> 05:35.000
Remember, the museum closes at 5 p.m.

05:35.000 --> 05:37.000
You only have half an hour.

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
The five friends walk around the museum.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
They look at the interesting exhibits.

05:43.000 --> 05:48.000
Look, here are the names of the Witches of 1692.

05:48.000 --> 05:51.000
And here are the pictures of the hangings.

05:51.000 --> 05:52.000
Says Nick.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
Look at this rope, says Bill.

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
How scary!

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
Say the girls.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.000
I'm going upstairs.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
Says Megan.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.000
Be careful.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.000
Says Kelly.

06:02.000 --> 06:03.000
Megan laughs.

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
I'm not afraid of witches or ghosts.

06:12.000 --> 06:15.000
There are no visitors upstairs.

06:15.000 --> 06:19.000
There is a sweet smell of roses in the air.

06:19.000 --> 06:22.000
Megan walks around and looks at everything.

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
Then she sees an old lady.

06:25.000 --> 06:30.000
She has a long black dress with small black buttons.

06:30.000 --> 06:35.000
Her skin is very white and her lips are very red.

06:35.000 --> 06:39.000
There is a strange red mark around her neck.

06:39.000 --> 06:41.000
She smiles at Megan.

06:41.000 --> 06:46.000
Megan smiles too, but she is nervous.

06:46.000 --> 06:49.000
Suddenly the air is very cold.

06:49.000 --> 06:51.000
How strange!

06:51.000 --> 06:52.000
She thinks.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.000
I want to go downstairs.

07:03.000 --> 07:06.000
When Kelly sees her, she asks.

07:06.000 --> 07:07.000
What's upstairs?

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
Oh, some interesting exhibits.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
Answers, Megan.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
The museum closes in five minutes.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.000
Says the attendant.

07:17.000 --> 07:23.000
Susan buys a book called Salem and the Witches of 1692.

07:23.000 --> 07:27.000
The three girls walk to the front door.

07:27.000 --> 07:30.000
Is there anyone still upstairs?

07:30.000 --> 07:31.000
Ask the attendant.

07:31.000 --> 07:32.000
Yes.

07:32.000 --> 07:33.000
Says Megan.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
There's an old lady.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.000
Really?

07:36.000 --> 07:37.000
Says the attendant.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.000
That's strange.

07:38.000 --> 07:42.000
You are the only visitors in the museum this afternoon.

07:42.000 --> 07:45.000
There aren't many visitors here on Fridays.

07:45.000 --> 07:47.000
There is an old lady upstairs.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.000
Says Megan.

07:49.000 --> 07:51.000
I'm going upstairs to see.

07:51.000 --> 07:53.000
Says the attendant.

07:53.000 --> 07:56.000
After a few minutes he returns.

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
His face is red and he says.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.000
Is this a joke?

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
There's no one upstairs.

08:02.000 --> 08:07.000
And the only door of the museum is this front door.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.000
Megan's friends look at her.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.000
She is silent.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.000
Then she says.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.000
Let's look outside.

08:15.000 --> 08:19.000
They run out of the museum and look outside.

08:19.000 --> 08:21.000
There's no one in the street.

08:21.000 --> 08:24.000
Only a black cat.

08:24.000 --> 08:31.000
After this strange experience they walk home.

08:31.000 --> 08:35.000
Now I have a lot of ideas for a Halloween party.

08:35.000 --> 08:36.000
Says Kelly.

08:36.000 --> 08:37.000
Yes, I do too.

08:37.000 --> 08:39.000
Says Susan.

08:39.000 --> 08:41.000
Very quiet, Megan.

08:41.000 --> 08:42.000
Says Bill.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
I'm thinking about the old lady at the museum.

08:56.000 --> 08:57.000
Hello.

08:57.000 --> 08:59.000
Is the museum still open?

08:59.000 --> 09:01.000
Yes, it is.

09:01.000 --> 09:03.000
Five tickets, please.

09:03.000 --> 09:04.000
Are you students?

09:04.000 --> 09:06.000
Yes, we are.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
Then you have a special price.

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
It's ten dollars for each student.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
Here you are.

09:12.000 --> 09:15.000
Do you have any information about the museum?

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
Yes, there are some books near the window over there.

09:19.000 --> 09:22.000
What time does the museum close?

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
It closes at five.

09:24.000 --> 09:32.000
The origins of Halloween.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Date.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
Twenty-two A.D.

09:36.000 --> 09:37.000
Place.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
British Isles.

09:39.000 --> 09:40.000
Hello.

09:40.000 --> 09:42.000
My name is Brennis.

09:42.000 --> 09:45.000
I'm a Selt and a Pagan.

09:45.000 --> 09:49.000
Let me tell you about an important Celtic festival.

09:49.000 --> 09:57.000
Samhain is the last day of summer and the last day of the Celtic year, October 31st.

09:57.000 --> 10:01.000
Samhain is the Celtic god of death.

10:01.000 --> 10:04.000
We are all afraid of him.

10:04.000 --> 10:10.000
On October 31st, we dress as witches, ghosts, and skeletons.

10:10.000 --> 10:13.000
We make fires to scare the evil spirits.

10:13.000 --> 10:17.000
We also play games to bring good luck in the new year.

10:17.000 --> 10:28.000
Oh, and the apples we eat are for good luck too.

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
Chapter 3.

10:30.000 --> 10:36.000
September 22nd, 1692.

10:36.000 --> 10:39.000
There is no school on Saturday.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
It is a cloudy autumn day.

10:43.000 --> 10:47.000
Autumn is usually a beautiful season in Salem.

10:47.000 --> 10:52.000
The leaves on the trees are yellow, red, and orange.

10:52.000 --> 10:57.000
Mr. and Mrs. Connor have a big orange pumpkin.

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
They are making a jack-o-lantern.

11:00.000 --> 11:04.000
When it's finished, we can put it in front of the window.

11:04.000 --> 11:05.000
Says Mr. Connor.

11:05.000 --> 11:08.000
Are you girls ready for Halloween?

11:08.000 --> 11:09.000
No, Dad.

11:09.000 --> 11:11.000
We must find a place for the party.

11:11.000 --> 11:12.000
Says Kelly.

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
We must make our costumes too.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.000
Says Megan.

11:15.000 --> 11:18.000
Today is a perfect day to do many things.

11:18.000 --> 11:20.000
Says Mrs. Connor.

11:20.000 --> 11:22.000
Finish your homework this morning.

11:22.000 --> 11:25.000
Then you can look for a place for the party this afternoon.

11:25.000 --> 11:28.000
I can start my science homework.

11:28.000 --> 11:29.000
Says Megan.

11:29.000 --> 11:31.000
I'm a study English.

11:31.000 --> 11:32.000
Says Kelly.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
I have a test on Wednesday.

11:34.000 --> 11:38.000
They go to their room and study until noon.

11:39.000 --> 11:41.000
Then the phone rings.

11:47.000 --> 11:48.000
Hello.

11:48.000 --> 11:49.000
This is Bill.

11:49.000 --> 11:51.000
I have a place for our party.

11:51.000 --> 11:52.000
Really?

11:52.000 --> 11:53.000
That's great.

11:53.000 --> 11:54.000
Where is it?

11:54.000 --> 11:55.000
Says Kelly.

11:55.000 --> 11:57.000
It's a surprise.

11:57.000 --> 12:00.000
Meet me and Nick in front of the school at 1.30pm.

12:00.000 --> 12:02.000
We can go together.

12:02.000 --> 12:03.000
Okay.

12:03.000 --> 12:04.000
At half past one then.

12:04.000 --> 12:05.000
Says Kelly.

12:08.000 --> 12:11.000
The five friends meet in front of their school.

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
They are very excited.

12:13.000 --> 12:14.000
Where is the place?

12:14.000 --> 12:15.000
Ask Susan.

12:15.000 --> 12:17.000
Follow me, says Bill.

12:17.000 --> 12:19.000
My grandmother knows this place.

12:19.000 --> 12:23.000
It is the best place for a spooky Halloween party.

12:23.000 --> 12:25.000
They walk past the park.

12:25.000 --> 12:28.000
Past the tennis courts and past the church.

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
Then they walk down a country road.

12:31.000 --> 12:35.000
At the end of the road they see an old cemetery.

12:35.000 --> 12:38.000
This is the oldest cemetery in Salem.

12:38.000 --> 12:39.000
Says Bill.

12:39.000 --> 12:42.000
They enter the old cemetery.

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
Look at the dates on the tombstones.

12:44.000 --> 12:49.000
This one says September 22, 1692.

12:49.000 --> 12:50.000
Says Megan.

12:50.000 --> 12:55.000
This one says September 22, 1692, too.

12:55.000 --> 12:56.000
Says Kelly.

12:56.000 --> 12:59.000
Here's another tombstone with the same date.

12:59.000 --> 13:02.000
September 22, 1692.

13:02.000 --> 13:03.000
Says Nick.

13:03.000 --> 13:06.000
They look at a lot of tombstones.

13:06.000 --> 13:10.000
These are probably the tombstones of the Salem witches.

13:10.000 --> 13:11.000
Says Bill.

13:11.000 --> 13:12.000
How spooky.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.000
Let's go now.

13:13.000 --> 13:15.000
Says Susan.

13:15.000 --> 13:19.000
The five friends run to the country road.

13:19.000 --> 13:21.000
Then they walk for a few minutes.

13:21.000 --> 13:26.000
At the end of the road they see an old abandoned house.

13:26.000 --> 13:28.000
It is near a forest.

13:28.000 --> 13:32.000
There is a rose bush near the door.

13:32.000 --> 13:34.000
This is the house for our party.

13:34.000 --> 13:35.000
Says Bill.

13:35.000 --> 13:38.000
His friends are very surprised.

13:38.000 --> 13:40.000
They look at the house.

13:40.000 --> 13:41.000
Wow!

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
Is this a haunted house?

13:43.000 --> 13:44.000
Nick asks.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
Bill laughs.

13:46.000 --> 13:49.000
This is a very old house.

13:49.000 --> 13:53.000
From the 1650s poor people sometimes live in it.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.000
But then they go away.

13:55.000 --> 13:57.000
It's abandoned.

13:57.000 --> 13:59.000
There is no electricity.

13:59.000 --> 14:01.000
Why is it abandoned?

14:01.000 --> 14:02.000
Asks Nick.

14:02.000 --> 14:05.000
They say strange things happen here.

14:05.000 --> 14:09.000
It's the perfect place for a spooky party.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
Remember, ghosts don't exist.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.000
Bill says.

14:13.000 --> 14:15.000
Are you sure?

14:15.000 --> 14:16.000
Asks Kelly.

14:16.000 --> 14:19.000
The five friends look at each other.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.000
There is something strange about this place.

14:22.000 --> 14:23.000
Says Nick.

14:23.000 --> 14:31.000
Chapter 4.

14:31.000 --> 14:34.000
The Abandoned House.

14:34.000 --> 14:43.000
Megan looks at the old house and says.

14:43.000 --> 14:46.000
Look at the writing above the door.

14:46.000 --> 14:50.000
Home of Abigail Cross.

14:50.000 --> 14:58.000
October 31st, 1627 to September 22nd, 1692.

14:58.000 --> 15:01.000
Who is Abigail Cross?

15:01.000 --> 15:03.000
Look at the date.

15:03.000 --> 15:07.000
September 22nd, 1692.

15:07.000 --> 15:10.000
Do you remember the tombstones?

15:10.000 --> 15:13.000
Many of them have the same date.

15:13.000 --> 15:15.000
You're right.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.000
Says Susan.

15:16.000 --> 15:22.000
Let me look in my new book, Salem and the Witches of 1692.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
After a few minutes, Susan says.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.000
Oh no!

15:27.000 --> 15:30.000
Abigail Cross is a witch.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
Her name is in this book.

15:32.000 --> 15:35.000
I don't like this old house.

15:35.000 --> 15:38.000
Let's find another place for the party.

15:38.000 --> 15:39.000
Says Kelly.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.000
You girls are silly.

15:41.000 --> 15:42.000
This is perfect.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.000
Says Bill.

15:43.000 --> 15:45.000
Come on, follow me.

15:45.000 --> 15:50.000
Bill is the first to enter the house.

15:50.000 --> 15:53.000
Nick and the girls follow.

15:53.000 --> 15:56.000
It is very cold inside.

15:56.000 --> 16:02.000
There is a big room with an old table, chairs and a cupboard.

16:02.000 --> 16:06.000
On the wall there is an old portrait of a woman.

16:06.000 --> 16:09.000
She is wearing a long black dress.

16:09.000 --> 16:12.000
She has a red rose in her hand.

16:12.000 --> 16:16.000
Her eyes are dark and evil.

16:16.000 --> 16:19.000
This portrait is very old.

16:19.000 --> 16:21.000
There's a date at the bottom.

16:21.000 --> 16:27.000
It says June 1659.

16:27.000 --> 16:29.000
Says Megan.

16:29.000 --> 16:32.000
It's probably a portrait of Abigail Cross.

16:32.000 --> 16:33.000
Says Nick.

16:33.000 --> 16:37.000
She's looking at us and she's smiling.

16:37.000 --> 16:38.000
Says Megan.

16:38.000 --> 16:41.000
What an evil smile.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.000
Says Susan.

16:42.000 --> 16:45.000
Everything here is so old and scary.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.000
Says Kelly.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.000
I like it.

16:47.000 --> 16:48.000
Says Nick.

16:48.000 --> 16:51.000
We can make spooky decorations and light candles.

16:51.000 --> 16:54.000
I can bring my portable radio for music.

16:54.000 --> 16:57.000
First we must clean this house.

16:57.000 --> 16:59.000
Then we can make the decorations.

16:59.000 --> 17:01.000
Says Susan.

17:01.000 --> 17:05.000
Nick and Bill go to buy some cleaning products.

17:05.000 --> 17:08.000
The girls talk about the party.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
How many chairs are there?

17:10.000 --> 17:11.000
Asks Kelly.

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
There are eight chairs.

17:13.000 --> 17:14.000
Answers Megan.

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
We must bring chairs from home.

17:16.000 --> 17:19.000
Fifteen of our friends are coming to the party.

17:19.000 --> 17:20.000
Says Susan.

17:20.000 --> 17:23.000
I want to look at the old kitchen.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.000
I want to look at the other rooms.

17:25.000 --> 17:27.000
Says Megan.

17:27.000 --> 17:32.000
She walks down a long corridor.

17:32.000 --> 17:37.000
She finds three rooms with some old furniture.

17:37.000 --> 17:44.000
Then she opens a small door and enters a dark bedroom.

17:44.000 --> 17:49.000
There is a sweet smell of roses.

17:49.000 --> 17:55.000
She sees a long black dress with small black buttons on a big bed.

17:55.000 --> 18:00.000
On the floor she sees a pair of old black boots.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
They are wet.

18:02.000 --> 18:05.000
She looks outside the window.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.000
It is raining.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
She looks in an old mirror.

18:10.000 --> 18:14.000
Someone in the mirror is looking at her.

18:14.000 --> 18:15.000
Megan is afraid.

18:15.000 --> 18:19.000
She wants to leave the room but her legs can't move.

18:19.000 --> 18:22.000
She wants to call Kelly and Susan.

18:22.000 --> 18:25.000
But she has no voice.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
Suddenly Kelly calls her.

18:28.000 --> 18:30.000
Megan, what are you doing?

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
Megan can't answer.

18:33.000 --> 18:36.000
Kelly and Susan run to the bedroom.

18:36.000 --> 18:39.000
Megan, what's happening?

18:39.000 --> 18:41.000
Megan's face is white.

18:41.000 --> 18:45.000
She points to the black dress and the wet boots.

18:45.000 --> 18:48.000
The girls are very surprised.

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
Do you remember the old lady at the museum?

18:51.000 --> 18:53.000
Megan whispers.

18:53.000 --> 18:57.000
This is her dress and those are her boots.

18:57.000 --> 18:59.000
Look, they're wet.

18:59.000 --> 19:02.000
Are you sure that old lady exists?

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
It's your imagination.

19:04.000 --> 19:05.000
Says Kelly.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.000
Megan is angry.

19:07.000 --> 19:09.000
It's not my imagination.

19:09.000 --> 19:12.000
This is Abigail Cross's house.

19:12.000 --> 19:14.000
And these are her clothes.

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
Abigail Cross is here.

19:16.000 --> 19:18.000
Abigail Cross is dead.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
But her ghost isn't.

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
Chapter 5.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
Halloween Costumes.

19:33.000 --> 19:37.000
Megan, Kelly and Susan go back to the big room.

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
They look at the old portrait.

19:41.000 --> 19:44.000
They don't like it.

19:44.000 --> 19:47.000
Soon the boys arrive with some cleaning products.

19:47.000 --> 19:49.000
And a broom.

19:49.000 --> 19:50.000
The girls say...

19:50.000 --> 19:54.000
Abigail Cross's dress and boots are in the bedroom.

19:54.000 --> 19:56.000
Someone wants to scare us.

19:56.000 --> 19:57.000
Says Bill.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.000
The door of the house is always open.

19:59.000 --> 20:01.000
Anyone can enter.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.000
This is a very old house.

20:03.000 --> 20:06.000
Old houses have old clothes.

20:06.000 --> 20:09.000
Nick is very quiet.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.000
Then he says...

20:10.000 --> 20:12.000
This is exciting.

20:12.000 --> 20:15.000
On Monday we can tell our friends about this place.

20:15.000 --> 20:17.000
Maybe we can see a ghost.

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
Ghosts.

20:19.000 --> 20:20.000
House Silly.

20:20.000 --> 20:21.000
Come on.

20:21.000 --> 20:23.000
Let's start cleaning.

20:23.000 --> 20:24.000
Says Bill.

20:24.000 --> 20:27.000
They clean the windows, the table and the chairs.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.000
It's 5 p.m.

20:29.000 --> 20:30.000
It's time to go home.

20:30.000 --> 20:31.000
Says Nick.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.000
I help my parents at the restaurant.

20:33.000 --> 20:36.000
The restaurant is always full on Saturdays.

20:36.000 --> 20:39.000
We can return tomorrow for the decorations.

20:39.000 --> 20:42.000
We must also talk about the games for the party.

20:42.000 --> 20:44.000
Says Susan.

20:44.000 --> 20:45.000
Okay.

20:45.000 --> 20:47.000
Let's meet here tomorrow at 1 p.m.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.000
Says Bill.

20:49.000 --> 20:51.000
Everyone goes home.

20:51.000 --> 20:56.000
After dinner, Mrs. Connor makes Halloween cookies and pumpkin pies.

20:56.000 --> 21:00.000
Mr. Connor puts the jack-o-lantern in front of the window.

21:00.000 --> 21:03.000
Kelly and Megan go to their room.

21:03.000 --> 21:06.000
They want to make their Halloween costumes.

21:06.000 --> 21:10.000
Do you think Abigail Cross is a ghost?

21:10.000 --> 21:11.000
Asks Kelly.

21:11.000 --> 21:13.000
I'm very confused.

21:13.000 --> 21:17.000
I don't know, but that house is evil.

21:17.000 --> 21:19.000
I don't want to be afraid.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.000
Says Kelly.

21:20.000 --> 21:23.000
I want to have fun at the Halloween party.

21:23.000 --> 21:24.000
You're right.

21:24.000 --> 21:26.000
Let's not talk about ghosts.

21:26.000 --> 21:27.000
Says Megan.

21:27.000 --> 21:30.000
The girls start making their Halloween costumes.

21:30.000 --> 21:32.000
I want to be an alien.

21:32.000 --> 21:33.000
Says Megan.

21:33.000 --> 21:35.000
Look at my green mask.

21:35.000 --> 21:36.000
It's nice.

21:36.000 --> 21:37.000
I like it.

21:37.000 --> 21:39.000
But what can I be?

21:39.000 --> 21:41.000
Kelly thinks for a long time.

21:41.000 --> 21:43.000
Then she says...

21:43.000 --> 21:46.000
I want to be Abigail Cross, the witch.

21:46.000 --> 21:47.000
No, Kelly.

21:47.000 --> 21:48.000
Don't do it.

21:48.000 --> 21:49.000
Says Megan.

21:49.000 --> 21:50.000
Why not?

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
It's an easy costume.

21:52.000 --> 21:55.000
I can wear mom's long black dress.

21:55.000 --> 21:57.000
Then I can buy a mask and a wig.

21:57.000 --> 21:59.000
I have a pair of old black boots.

21:59.000 --> 22:01.000
I want to scare everyone.

22:01.000 --> 22:02.000
Kelly laughs.

22:02.000 --> 22:04.000
Aren't you afraid?

22:04.000 --> 22:05.000
Asks Megan.

22:05.000 --> 22:08.000
No, it's just a Halloween costume.

22:08.000 --> 22:09.000
Says Kelly.

22:09.000 --> 22:11.000
Remember, our costumes are a secret.

22:11.000 --> 22:13.000
Don't tell anyone.

22:13.000 --> 22:19.000
On Sunday afternoon, the five friends meet at the abandoned house.

22:19.000 --> 22:22.000
When they enter, they look at the portrait.

22:22.000 --> 22:25.000
The woman has the same evil smile.

22:25.000 --> 22:29.000
But there is something different in the portrait.

22:29.000 --> 22:31.000
Megan sees it.

22:31.000 --> 22:33.000
She turns on her torch and says...

22:33.000 --> 22:36.000
Look at the woman in the portrait.

22:36.000 --> 22:39.000
She has a red mark around her neck.

22:39.000 --> 22:40.000
You're right.

22:40.000 --> 22:41.000
Says Nick.

22:41.000 --> 22:43.000
They all look at the portrait.

22:43.000 --> 22:45.000
What does it mean?

22:45.000 --> 22:47.000
It's your imagination, says Bill.

22:47.000 --> 22:50.000
You can see the red mark because you have a torch.

22:50.000 --> 22:53.000
Who wants to go downstairs and see the basement?

22:53.000 --> 22:55.000
Asks Bill.

22:55.000 --> 22:58.000
We can use the basement for scary games.

22:58.000 --> 23:00.000
You boys can go to the basement.

23:00.000 --> 23:01.000
Says Susan.

23:01.000 --> 23:05.000
We want to move the old tables to the center of the room.

23:05.000 --> 23:08.000
Megan goes to the dark bedroom.

23:08.000 --> 23:13.000
She opens the door and looks inside.

23:14.000 --> 23:19.000
The black dress and the black boots are still there.

23:19.000 --> 23:21.000
She shuts the door quickly.

23:21.000 --> 23:24.000
Her heart is beating fast.

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
When the boys return, they say...

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
There is nothing in the basement.

23:28.000 --> 23:31.000
Only some old barrels.

23:37.000 --> 23:41.000
Megan, Kelly, and Susan go back to the big room.

23:41.000 --> 23:44.000
They look at the old portrait.

23:44.000 --> 23:46.000
They don't like it.

23:46.000 --> 23:51.000
Soon the boys arrive with some cleaning products and a broom.

23:51.000 --> 23:53.000
The girls say...

23:53.000 --> 23:57.000
Abigail crosses dress and boots are in the bedroom.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
Someone wants to scare us.

23:59.000 --> 24:00.000
Says Bill.

24:00.000 --> 24:03.000
The door of the house is always open.

24:03.000 --> 24:05.000
Anyone can enter.

24:05.000 --> 24:08.000
This is a very old house.

24:08.000 --> 24:11.000
Old houses have old clothes.

24:11.000 --> 24:13.000
Nick is very quiet.

24:13.000 --> 24:15.000
Then he says...

24:15.000 --> 24:17.000
This is exciting.

24:17.000 --> 24:20.000
On Monday we can tell our friends about this place.

24:20.000 --> 24:23.000
Maybe we can see a ghost.

24:23.000 --> 24:27.000
Now turn to page 34 and check.

24:33.000 --> 24:35.000
Salem Halloween Cookies.

24:35.000 --> 24:39.000
It's fun to organize a Halloween party in your home.

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
It's easy too.

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
First, find a big room you can use.

24:44.000 --> 24:47.000
Second, make some scary decorations.

24:47.000 --> 24:50.000
Third, prepare some Halloween food.

24:50.000 --> 24:55.000
Popcorn, apples, sweets, pumpkin pies,

24:55.000 --> 24:58.000
and special Halloween cookies.

24:58.000 --> 25:01.000
Make Salem Halloween cookies for your party.

25:01.000 --> 25:02.000
It's easy.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.000
Just follow the recipe.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.000
Ingredients.

25:06.000 --> 25:10.000
Three-quarters of a cup of chopped nuts.

25:10.000 --> 25:13.000
One cup softened butter.

25:13.000 --> 25:16.000
Half a cup of powdered sugar.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
Half a cup flour.

25:18.000 --> 25:21.000
One teaspoon vanilla extract.

25:21.000 --> 25:24.000
Quarter of a teaspoon salt.

25:24.000 --> 25:26.000
Powdered sugar.

25:26.000 --> 25:28.000
Utensils to use.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.000
A big bowl.

25:30.000 --> 25:31.000
A wooden spoon.

25:31.000 --> 25:33.000
A teaspoon.

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
A nonstick cookie sheet.

25:35.000 --> 25:39.000
Now chop the nuts.

25:39.000 --> 25:42.000
Mix together nuts, butter, sugar,

25:42.000 --> 25:44.000
and vanilla in the bowl.

25:44.000 --> 25:48.000
Slowly add flour and salt.

25:48.000 --> 25:52.000
Put the bowl in the refrigerator for one hour.

25:52.000 --> 25:54.000
Then make little balls.

25:54.000 --> 25:59.000
About two and a half centimeters in diameter.

25:59.000 --> 26:03.000
Roll each ball in powdered sugar three times.

26:03.000 --> 26:05.000
Put the balls on a cookie sheet.

26:05.000 --> 26:07.000
Bake in the oven,

26:07.000 --> 26:10.000
175 degrees Celsius,

26:10.000 --> 26:12.000
for 30 minutes.

26:12.000 --> 26:14.000
Happy Halloween.

26:19.000 --> 26:21.000
Chapter 6.

26:21.000 --> 26:24.000
Mysterious names.

26:24.000 --> 26:27.000
The girls look at the floor.

26:27.000 --> 26:29.000
This floor is very dirty.

26:29.000 --> 26:33.000
It is made of stone and it's difficult to clean.

26:33.000 --> 26:36.000
Let's wash it with hot water and detergent.

26:36.000 --> 26:38.000
Says Susan.

26:38.000 --> 26:45.000
So Susan and Kelly wash the stone floor.

26:45.000 --> 26:48.000
Suddenly Susan stops washing.

26:48.000 --> 26:52.000
She looks at the stones and says...

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
I can't believe this.

26:54.000 --> 26:57.000
There are names on these stones.

26:57.000 --> 26:59.000
Her friends come and look.

26:59.000 --> 27:03.000
One name is George Johnson.

27:03.000 --> 27:07.000
Then there's Rebecca Putnam and Sarah Morley.

27:07.000 --> 27:10.000
This is very strange, says Bill.

27:10.000 --> 27:12.000
Look at the other names.

27:12.000 --> 27:15.000
He reads them and then he counts them.

27:15.000 --> 27:17.000
There are twenty.

27:17.000 --> 27:19.000
This is a mystery.

27:19.000 --> 27:21.000
Who wrote them?

27:21.000 --> 27:23.000
What do they mean?

27:23.000 --> 27:25.000
Can you repeat the names?

27:25.000 --> 27:27.000
Perhaps I can find them in my book.

27:27.000 --> 27:29.000
Says Susan.

27:29.000 --> 27:31.000
Bill tells her the names.

27:31.000 --> 27:34.000
She finds all of them in her book.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.000
How spooky.

27:36.000 --> 27:41.000
These are the names of the twenty witches of the hangings of 1692.

27:41.000 --> 27:45.000
There are seven men and thirteen women.

27:45.000 --> 27:47.000
Look at this page.

27:47.000 --> 27:52.000
The Salem witch hangings of 1692.

27:52.000 --> 27:54.000
June 10th.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.000
One hanging.

27:56.000 --> 27:58.000
July 19th.

27:58.000 --> 28:00.000
Five hangings.

28:00.000 --> 28:02.000
August 19th.

28:02.000 --> 28:04.000
Five hangings.

28:04.000 --> 28:06.000
September 19th.

28:06.000 --> 28:07.000
One hanging.

28:07.000 --> 28:10.000
September 22nd.

28:10.000 --> 28:12.000
Eight hangings.

28:12.000 --> 28:13.000
What can we do?

28:13.000 --> 28:14.000
Asks Kelly.

28:14.000 --> 28:16.000
Nothing says Bill.

28:16.000 --> 28:19.000
Are you afraid of names on stones?

28:19.000 --> 28:22.000
These are not the names of ordinary people.

28:22.000 --> 28:25.000
These are the names of twenty witches.

28:25.000 --> 28:26.000
Says Megan.

28:26.000 --> 28:29.000
Witches have magic powers.

28:29.000 --> 28:31.000
We can show our friends at the party.

28:31.000 --> 28:33.000
We can scare them.

28:33.000 --> 28:35.000
Says Nick laughing.

28:35.000 --> 28:37.000
That's a great idea.

28:37.000 --> 28:39.000
This Halloween party is exciting.

28:39.000 --> 28:40.000
Says Bill.

28:40.000 --> 28:43.000
Let's put the decorations on the walls.

28:43.000 --> 28:46.000
There are bats, spiders, and pumpkins.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.000
Who wants to bring the food and drinks?

28:48.000 --> 28:50.000
Asks Nick.

28:50.000 --> 28:54.000
Megan and I can bring pumpkin pies and Halloween cookies.

28:54.000 --> 28:55.000
Says Kelly.

28:55.000 --> 28:58.000
I can bring apple pies, popcorn, and sweets.

28:58.000 --> 28:59.000
Says Susan.

28:59.000 --> 29:02.000
Let me bring drinks and candles.

29:02.000 --> 29:04.000
Says Bill.

29:04.000 --> 29:08.000
Then I can bring paper plates, paper cups, and a paper table cloth.

29:08.000 --> 29:10.000
I can also bring some chairs.

29:10.000 --> 29:11.000
Says Nick.

29:11.000 --> 29:13.000
Don't forget your portable radio, Nick.

29:13.000 --> 29:14.000
Says Kelly.

29:14.000 --> 29:15.000
Okay.

29:15.000 --> 29:18.000
So everything is ready for the party, says Bill.

29:18.000 --> 29:21.000
We must be here at eight o'clock to prepare things.

29:21.000 --> 29:25.000
The party starts at nine p.m.

29:25.000 --> 29:31.000
It's Monday, October 31st, Halloween.

29:31.000 --> 29:37.000
There are Halloween decorations in the homes, in the shops, and in the classrooms.

29:37.000 --> 29:44.000
When school finishes, Kelly buys a wig and a mask of an old lady.

29:44.000 --> 29:48.000
That evening, Kelly and Megan put on their costumes.

29:48.000 --> 29:51.000
When Mrs. Connor sees them, she says.

29:51.000 --> 29:53.000
What wonderful costumes.

29:53.000 --> 29:57.000
A green alien and an old lady.

29:57.000 --> 30:00.000
I'm not an ordinary old lady.

30:00.000 --> 30:04.000
I'm a Salem witch, and the year is 1692.

30:04.000 --> 30:05.000
Says Kelly.

30:05.000 --> 30:06.000
Wow.

30:06.000 --> 30:07.000
Says Mr. Connor.

30:07.000 --> 30:09.000
Where is the party?

30:09.000 --> 30:13.000
It's at the abandoned house near the old cemetery.

30:13.000 --> 30:15.000
That's exciting.

30:15.000 --> 30:16.000
Have fun.

30:16.000 --> 30:17.000
Says Mr. Connor.

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
Goodbye, girls.

30:19.000 --> 30:20.000
Have fun.

30:20.000 --> 30:27.000
Says Mrs. Connor.

30:27.000 --> 30:29.000
Chapter seven.

30:29.000 --> 30:36.000
The House of Horrors.

30:36.000 --> 30:40.000
The five friends meet at eight that evening.

30:40.000 --> 30:43.000
Everyone has a scary costume.

30:43.000 --> 30:45.000
Bill is a vampire.

30:45.000 --> 30:47.000
Nick is a skeleton.

30:47.000 --> 30:50.000
Susan is a ghost.

30:50.000 --> 30:54.000
When they see Kelly's costume, they laugh and say.

30:54.000 --> 30:59.000
Good evening Mrs. Abigail Ross.

30:59.000 --> 31:03.000
They cover the old table with a paper table cloth.

31:03.000 --> 31:07.000
Then they put the food and drinks on the table.

31:07.000 --> 31:17.000
They light the candles because there is no electricity.

31:17.000 --> 31:20.000
Nick turns on his portable radio.

31:20.000 --> 31:23.000
Meghan goes to the dark bedroom.

31:23.000 --> 31:27.000
She opens the door and looks inside.

31:27.000 --> 31:33.000
The black dress and black boots are not there.

31:33.000 --> 31:37.000
She is afraid, but she says nothing to her friends.

31:37.000 --> 31:39.000
Soon their friends arrive.

31:39.000 --> 31:43.000
They all have scary costumes and masks.

31:43.000 --> 31:46.000
Is this a haunted house?

31:46.000 --> 31:48.000
It's very spooky.

31:48.000 --> 31:51.000
They say no one answers.

31:51.000 --> 31:54.000
Some boys and girls dance.

31:54.000 --> 31:57.000
Others eat, talk, and laugh.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.000
Several hours pass.

31:59.000 --> 32:01.000
Everyone is happy.

32:02.000 --> 32:04.000
It's a great party.

32:04.000 --> 32:07.000
They say.

32:07.000 --> 32:10.000
It's time for the treasure hunt.

32:10.000 --> 32:13.000
Says Bill, you all have different maps.

32:13.000 --> 32:16.000
Let's start.

32:16.000 --> 32:19.000
Everyone starts in a different room.

32:19.000 --> 32:21.000
Some start in the kitchen.

32:21.000 --> 32:24.000
Others start in the bedrooms.

32:24.000 --> 32:29.000
Kelly takes her torch and goes downstairs to the basement.

32:29.000 --> 32:33.000
She looks inside a big barrel.

32:33.000 --> 32:35.000
It is very dark.

32:35.000 --> 32:39.000
And Kelly is in the basement alone.

32:39.000 --> 32:44.000
Suddenly there is a sweet smell of roses.

32:44.000 --> 32:48.000
She turns on her torch and she is terrified.

32:48.000 --> 32:52.000
The old lady from the museum is standing by the barrel.

32:52.000 --> 32:55.000
You are not Abigail Cross.

32:55.000 --> 32:58.000
I am Abigail Cross.

32:58.000 --> 33:02.000
Tonight is Halloween and you are in my house.

33:02.000 --> 33:06.000
On this night we spirits look for young bodies.

33:06.000 --> 33:10.000
When we find a young body we can live again.

33:10.000 --> 33:14.000
At midnight my spirit enters your body.

33:14.000 --> 33:18.000
You must die so that I can live.

33:18.000 --> 33:21.000
Kelly's heart is beating fast.

33:21.000 --> 33:24.000
Her legs can't move.

33:24.000 --> 33:26.000
She has no voice.

33:26.000 --> 33:31.000
Abigail Cross touches Kelly with her cold hand.

33:31.000 --> 33:35.000
She takes off Kelly's mask and wig.

33:35.000 --> 33:38.000
Your bed is in the barrel.

33:38.000 --> 33:40.000
You are tired.

33:40.000 --> 33:43.000
You must sleep forever.

33:43.000 --> 33:45.000
Kelly obeys.

33:45.000 --> 33:48.000
She goes to sleep inside the barrel.

33:48.000 --> 33:53.000
Abigail puts on Kelly's mask and wig.

33:53.000 --> 33:56.000
She goes upstairs to the party.

34:02.000 --> 34:05.000
At half past 11 Nick says...

34:05.000 --> 34:07.000
It's almost midnight.

34:07.000 --> 34:10.000
Let's sit down and take off our masks.

34:10.000 --> 34:13.000
We want to see the person behind the mask.

34:13.000 --> 34:15.000
Nick asks...

34:15.000 --> 34:17.000
Who is the alien?

34:17.000 --> 34:19.000
The alien takes off her mask.

34:19.000 --> 34:21.000
It's Megan!

34:21.000 --> 34:23.000
Everyone laughs.

34:23.000 --> 34:25.000
And who is the ghost?

34:25.000 --> 34:28.000
It's Susan!

34:28.000 --> 34:30.000
Who is the old lady?

34:30.000 --> 34:32.000
asks Bill.

34:32.000 --> 34:35.000
The old lady takes off her mask.

34:35.000 --> 34:37.000
Everyone screams.

34:37.000 --> 34:40.000
It's Abigail Cross's ghost.

34:40.000 --> 34:43.000
Her face is white and her eyes are red.

34:43.000 --> 34:46.000
She has a red mark around her neck.

34:46.000 --> 34:50.000
She laughs and her teeth are black.

34:50.000 --> 34:52.000
Everyone is terrified.

34:52.000 --> 34:54.000
Bill looks at her and says...

34:54.000 --> 34:56.000
That's Kelly's costume.

34:56.000 --> 34:57.000
Where is Kelly?

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
I am Kelly.

34:59.000 --> 35:03.000
At midnight my spirit enters her body.

35:03.000 --> 35:05.000
Remember, I am a witch.

35:05.000 --> 35:08.000
Everyone wants to run away.

35:08.000 --> 35:12.000
They go to the door, but they cannot open it.

35:12.000 --> 35:17.000
There are the horrible faces of the other ghosts outside the windows.

35:17.000 --> 35:20.000
The ghosts are looking inside.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
Who are these people?

35:22.000 --> 35:23.000
asks Bill.

35:23.000 --> 35:29.000
They are the witches of the hangings of 1692.

35:29.000 --> 35:32.000
Look at the red mark on my neck.

35:32.000 --> 35:35.000
This is the mark of the rope.

35:35.000 --> 35:40.000
20 witches for 20 young bodies.

35:40.000 --> 35:43.000
Now you are in my house.

35:43.000 --> 35:47.000
This is the house of horrors.

35:47.000 --> 35:51.000
No one leaves this house alive.

35:51.000 --> 35:55.000
At midnight our spirits enter your bodies.

35:55.000 --> 35:57.000
We want to live again.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.000
We want to bring evil to Salem.

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
Says Abigail Cross.

36:02.000 --> 36:03.000
Where is Kelly?

36:03.000 --> 36:04.000
asks Bill.

36:04.000 --> 36:07.000
Look at the portrait on the wall.

36:07.000 --> 36:09.000
laughs the witch.

36:09.000 --> 36:12.000
Everyone looks at the portrait.

36:12.000 --> 36:15.000
They see Kelly's face.

36:15.000 --> 36:17.000
Her lips are red.

36:17.000 --> 36:20.000
And there is a red mark around her neck.

36:20.000 --> 36:24.000
This is our party, not yours.

36:24.000 --> 36:26.000
Screams the witch.

36:32.000 --> 36:36.000
They meet at the old house.

36:36.000 --> 36:40.000
Everyone is wearing scary costumes.

36:40.000 --> 36:43.000
The boys light candles.

36:43.000 --> 36:47.000
Everyone is ready for the party.

36:47.000 --> 36:53.000
Megan goes to the bedroom, but she sees nobody there.

36:53.000 --> 36:56.000
Soon their friends arrive.

36:56.000 --> 36:58.000
The party starts.

36:58.000 --> 37:01.000
Everyone is happy.

37:01.000 --> 37:04.000
Then there is a treasure hunt.

37:04.000 --> 37:10.000
Kelly goes downstairs and looks inside a big barrel.

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
Chapter 8.

37:17.000 --> 37:20.000
Fire.

37:20.000 --> 37:25.000
Suddenly the decorations on the wall start moving.

37:25.000 --> 37:28.000
The bats are flying around the room.

37:28.000 --> 37:31.000
They are making strange noises.

37:31.000 --> 37:33.000
Screams a girl.

37:33.000 --> 37:35.000
There is a bat in my hair.

37:35.000 --> 37:37.000
Screams a boy.

37:37.000 --> 37:39.000
This bat is a vampire.

37:39.000 --> 37:42.000
Slowly the ghosts enter the house.

37:42.000 --> 37:45.000
They penetrate the walls.

37:45.000 --> 37:48.000
They are really spooky.

37:48.000 --> 37:51.000
They move around their victims.

37:51.000 --> 37:54.000
Megan and Susan are terrified and say...

37:54.000 --> 37:56.000
They are waiting for midnight.

37:56.000 --> 37:59.000
Do you remember the 20 names on the floor?

37:59.000 --> 38:02.000
These are their ghosts.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.000
We must find Kelly.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.000
Says Megan.

38:05.000 --> 38:08.000
A candle on the table falls.

38:08.000 --> 38:13.000
The paper tablecloth is burning.

38:13.000 --> 38:14.000
Fire.

38:14.000 --> 38:16.000
We must get out of here.

38:16.000 --> 38:17.000
Says Bill.

38:17.000 --> 38:19.000
Oh no, it's a big fire.

38:19.000 --> 38:20.000
Says Susan.

38:20.000 --> 38:22.000
We can't open the door.

38:22.000 --> 38:23.000
Says Nick.

38:23.000 --> 38:24.000
It's five to midnight.

38:24.000 --> 38:27.000
At midnight the ghosts take our bodies.

38:27.000 --> 38:28.000
What can we do?

38:28.000 --> 38:30.000
I must find Kelly.

38:30.000 --> 38:31.000
Says Bill.

38:31.000 --> 38:35.000
He takes his torch and runs to the basement.

38:35.000 --> 38:37.000
He looks in all the barrels.

38:37.000 --> 38:40.000
Finally, he sees Kelly.

38:40.000 --> 38:41.000
She is sleeping.

38:41.000 --> 38:43.000
Kelly! Kelly!

38:43.000 --> 38:44.000
Says Bill.

38:44.000 --> 38:46.000
Wake up! Wake up!

38:46.000 --> 38:48.000
Kelly does not wake up.

38:48.000 --> 38:49.000
Kelly!

38:49.000 --> 38:51.000
Says Bill. Kelly!

38:51.000 --> 38:57.000
Bill takes Kelly in his arms and carries her upstairs.

38:57.000 --> 39:00.000
It's two minutes to midnight.

39:00.000 --> 39:02.000
There is fire everywhere.

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
The room is full of black smoke.

39:05.000 --> 39:08.000
Everyone is terrified.

39:08.000 --> 39:11.000
Bats and spiders are flying in the air.

39:11.000 --> 39:15.000
The ghosts are waiting for midnight.

39:15.000 --> 39:18.000
No one can open the door or the windows.

39:19.000 --> 39:22.000
Suddenly, the portrait is burning.

39:22.000 --> 39:26.000
The fire is destroying the evil spirit.

39:26.000 --> 39:27.000
Look!

39:27.000 --> 39:28.000
