43:11.000 --> 43:13.000
She is sleeping.

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
Make a bat.

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
You need...

43:22.000 --> 43:24.000
A square piece of paper.

43:24.000 --> 43:28.000
Colored on one side and white on the other side.

43:28.000 --> 43:31.000
A pair of scissors.

43:31.000 --> 43:33.000
One.

43:33.000 --> 43:37.000
Fold the square in half from top to bottom.

43:37.000 --> 43:39.000
Two.

43:39.000 --> 43:44.000
Fold and unfold in half from side to side.

43:44.000 --> 43:46.000
Three.

43:46.000 --> 43:49.000
Fold one half up along the middle fold line.

43:49.000 --> 43:53.000
Start to open out the paper.

43:53.000 --> 43:54.000
Four.

43:54.000 --> 43:59.000
And with your free hand, press it down.

43:59.000 --> 44:01.000
Five.

44:01.000 --> 44:05.000
Neatly into a triangle.

44:05.000 --> 44:06.000
Six.

44:06.000 --> 44:08.000
Turn the paper over.

44:08.000 --> 44:12.000
Repeat steps two to five.

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
Seven.

44:14.000 --> 44:18.000
Fold one of the right hand corners to the middle fold line.

44:18.000 --> 44:22.000
Do the same with the other left hand corner.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
Eight.

44:24.000 --> 44:28.000
Fold the right bottom corners in to make the bat's feet.

44:28.000 --> 44:32.000
Nine.

44:32.000 --> 44:35.000
Carefully cut the paper as shown.

44:35.000 --> 44:42.000
Fold the top point down so making the bat's head and ears appear.

44:42.000 --> 44:43.000
Ten.

44:43.000 --> 44:49.000
To complete the bat, fold the tips of its feet out towards you.

44:49.000 --> 44:54.000
Don't forget to draw the eyes and fangs!

